rationale: EST timing is very approximate, based on visual clues guide ( <https://docs.google.com/document/d/1aoUBFlERClHrNOoufBMiC7p0M15PrvyjM371sIG02Jw/edit?usp=sharing> ). By the 6 minute mark of the video, the Blue Trump flag is hanging to the right of the inauguration balcony on the back wall of the West Plaza, though it was not there at the beginning of the video. There is a time stamped photo of this flag at 3:03pm, but it was not hanging at 2:45pm. The CapitolFlagCalledFreedom hangs on the back of the scaffolding from the beginning of the footage. Thus the footage must begin after 2:53 and 3:03 occurs on or after the 6 minute mark.

rationale:
Note: This is calculated from previously calculated footage, not a primary source. Therefore error may be larger. Also, I would add an approximately one minute error margin (though hopefully much smaller) due to people's variable walking speed.   
  
As a point of reference, note the respective exits from the tunnel area of #EmoNazi (at 1:07) and #SeattleUWGuy (at 5:44) in the current video ( <https://jan6archive.com/youtube/L4AADYTHDTE.mp4> ) -- these both align with their appearances on the outside steps in the video Storming the Capitol Part II from Albert Meyer (at 4:18 and 8:52, respectively)  ( <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rAKBMFMuJ-g)>. The "Storming" video was previously calculated to have a start time of 14:56:16 Eastern.   
  
Notice that in both videos the time between the two suspects’ tunnel exits is nearly exactly 4 minutes and 35 seconds, making it very unlikely that these videos are capturing a different set of tunnel exits by the two suspects. I assume a 30 second struggle to get from tunnel exit point seen in this video to the halfway down the steps point where the "Storming" video captures them. So, adding that 30 seconds, we can assume that minute marker 1:37 in this video aligns with minute marker 4:18 in the Storming video. Thus the realtime for moment of alignment is 15:00:34.   
  
With all these assumptions in mind, the start time of this L4AADY video is therefore approximately 14:58:57 Eastern.

This timestamp will be used as it aligns with official security footage.  
  
TIMESTAMP CALCULATION 2: This video was lined up with a 16:27:06 timestamped image from Lev Radin (https://www.pacificpressagency.com/preview/1300303). The image appears to align with the 1:06 minute mark on the video, which means this video takes place from 16:26-16:31. As a reference point, note the positions of #Slickback and #PippiLongScarf's hands. There are no gaps or cuts in video, so the realtime should be okay to use for the entire thing.  This calculation indicates that Lev Radin's camera is about 13 seconds behind Police bodycam footage. summary: #PippiLongScarf #PlaidLad #HarleyJacketBatonMan #CatSweat
- Someone in the mob throws something at the police officers lining the Tunnel Entrance. #Slickback ducks.

- #WhiteDeathHoodie clambers toward the left window from the mouth of the tunnel, past Justin Winchell - Rosanne Boyland's friend who can be seen in the teal jacket bending over someone (likely Roseanne).

- Many people have fallen at the top of the Tunnel Entrance Steps. #WhiteDeathHoodie continues to make his way north (toward the left-hand window). #LittleBrownBeard is moving closer to the tunnel entrance.
- #HockeyStickMan throws a white tube at the police line.

- The white tube catches in the tunnel entrance, spanning the width of it for a moment. This is a useful moment for aligning with other footage for time-alignment purposes. #LittleBrownBeard reaches into the Tunnel Entrance.
- someone sprays bear spray at the police line.
- Roseanne Boyland's friend in the teal jacket can be seen gesturing for help. #Fingerman has a large stick and is leaning toward the tunnel entrance.
- #Violence escalating.
- #BaldEagle removes his eagle mask.
- #Scallops stabs at an officer with crutches. From the other side of the steps someone throws a can at the line of officers.
- #CowboyScreech jabs at officers with a stick.
- The crowd cheers as the police continue to be attacked by #Scallops and others
- #HockeyStickMan beats at the police line with a hockey stick.
- #OrangeNTeal is climbing over the railing at the left side of the steps. #Slickback is raising his hand. The police have grabbed #Scallops' crutches.
- #LittleBrownBeard is looking into the tunnel again - it cannot be seen yet but a rioter is trapped inside behind the police line.

- #Scallops climbs over the railing at the top right of the Tunnel Entrance steps. He pushes and kicks police, grabbing at their batons. #HockeyStickMan continues to beat police with his hockey stick.
- #Scallops grabs an officer (later identified as Officer 5586 B.A. Miller), dragging him to the ground and down the steps.
- #OrangeNTeal appears to come to assist in dragging the officer.
- At the very edge of the screen, #Caveman begins to beat Officer Miller with the flagpole.
- #LittleBrownBeard is bending over something at the top of the steps.
- People in the crowd cheer the mob on, with shouts like "Fuck the police!"
- #LittleBrownBeard peers around the Tunnel opening again.
- #HighFiveCowboy raises the crutch. #Caveman climbs toward the top of the steps.
-  #PufferJacketCurlyHair kneels down to crawl and retrieve Rosanne Boyland along with a second man
- Someone throws a pole or broom at the police line. On the right hand side, people continue to attack police.

- A hand reaches out of the left side of the tunnel. #LittleBrownBeard grabs it, pulls the man out - it is #BlackHatStripedBuff. LBB immediately rips off Buff's hat, grabs him by the jacket and shoves him down the stairs, yelling at him. As Buff has been in the tunnel behind the police line for quite sometime, LBB may be angry that Buff very nearly got himself caught and arrested.
- A shaggy hair blond male with black shirt with white cuffs is seen shouting for help from below and the sounds of “medic, medic” become audible by 2:38
- The #ThreePercentSheriff is at the top of the steps. Police spray bear spray. This repels the mob fairly effectively.

- Though people have been going in and out of the lower panel of the window to the left of the tunnel for some time (since it was broken around 4:11pm), someone climbs up on the sill to smash the upper panel with a baseball bat.
- Justin Winchell is now seen with Rosanne and again signaling for help from below as #CommanderBlueHoodie turns his attention to a riotous colleague to offer him water for an eye flush.

- A person wearing a black jacket and reflective glasses with a light green army balaclava headgear is seen administering chest compressions. He is later one of the individuals that helps to move Roseanne back to the police lines.
- The upper window panel in the window to the left of the tunnel entrance is smashed in.
- #BlueHoodieGreyHat attempts with an individual with burgundy shirt who's been one of the relentless attackers now negotiating with police to summon professional help.
- The crowd can be herad singing the Star Spangled Banner "...gave proof through the night that our flag was still there."
- #LittleBrownBeard stands by the window left of the tunnel. Several people seem to come up and talk to him.
- More people climb into the room through the newly broken window (there were already others inside via the window below it)
- #OrangeHoodieRedHat and #LittleBrownBeard pass each other near the window. They may have a brief conversation, or LBB could be talking to #LittleBlondeGreyHood

- #CommanderBlueHoodie and others drag an unconscious body from the top of the stairs by the left railing back toward police. The person is wearing grey shoes and jeans. As she and her friend were in this area in earlier footage, and she was seen wearing similar clothing, it is very likely that this was Rosanne Boyland, who was trampled to death. While some bring Roseanne back to the police to receive medical treatment, still others attack MPD Officers.

- Rosanne Boyland's friend - Justin Winchell stands and wipes his face. At the top of the steps, the police and others seem to be hunching over something and some yell at the mob to stop. I would speculate that the person they are hunching over is Roseanne Boyland whom Justin has just dragged back to the police line after CPR has failed.
- #LittleBrownBeard yanks at the expensive camera equipment of the cameraman by the left window (Tomas Abad, I believe), pulling him down the steps with it.
